# git aliases I use

git aliases allow you to type less characters for a command. Here are a  few aliases that I am using right now. I'll present them in two formats:

	* configuration file view : as they would  appear in your .gitconfig file.
	* command-line commands : the commands you would make on the git bash command line to add the aliases to your global configuration.


## Configuration File View

[alias]
	st = status
	co = checkout
	lg = log --color --graph --pretty=format:'%Cred%h%Creset -%C(yellow)%d%Creset %s %Cgreen(%cr) %C(bold blue)<%an>%Creset' --abbrev-commit


## Command-Line Commands

	$ git config --global alias.st status

	$ git config --global alias.co checkout

	$ git config --global alias.lg "log --color --graph --pretty=format:'%Cred%h%Creset -%C(yellow)%d%Creset %s %Cgreen(%cr) %C(bold blue)<%an>%Creset' --abbrev-commit"

	You should copy and paste that last command (it's all one command) rather than try to type it out to avoid error.
	
	Reference: for the git lg alias, I obtained this nice alias from https://coderwall.com/p/euwpig

